n good health after 12-week passage. Fellow passengers included William Wadsworth, Tobie Willet (possible relation to Mary Willet who married Rev. Samuel Hooker), James Olmstedd, and others of Hooker's Company."},"hartford_land":{"inventory_date":"February 1639/40","parcels":9,"notes":"Nine parcels originally granted: dwelling house on east side of Main Street abutting Centinel Hill; seven acres east of Great River; five acres in North Meadow; forty-seven acres meadow/swamp in North Meadow; one acre in Little Meadow; thirty acres in Old Oxpasture; seventeen acres in Cow Pasture; eleven acres in Venturers Field; sixteen acres in Neck of Land. Also gained 25 additional parcels by acquisition."},"will":{"date":{"year":1659,"month":8,"day":12},"codicil_date":{"year":1660,"month":1,"day":17},"bequests_summary":"Dwelling house and lands to wife Dorothy for her natural life; then to son John. Wethersfield property to son Samuel. Grandchildren John Russell (£20), John Talcott, Samuel Talcott, Elizabeth Talcott (£5 each). £5 to Rev. Samuel Stone; £5 toward a Latin school at Hartford. Overseers: Richard Lord Sr. and son John.","gift_to_stone":"Five pounds to 'my reverend and beloved teacher, Mr. Stone' — Rev. Samuel Stone, Hartford minister and colleague of Thomas Hooker"},"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"X00007","display_label":"Tobie Willet was a fellow passenger on the Lion in.","link_text":"Capt. Thomas Willet"},{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"I00006","display_label":"Tobie Willet was a fellow passenger on the Lion in.","link_text":"Mary Willet Buckingham"},{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"H00007","display_label":"Tobie Willet was a fellow passenger on the Lion in.","link_text":"Rev. Samuel Hooker"},{"type":"civic_peer","related_id":"H00001","display_label":"co-founded Hartford with Talcott","link_text":"Rev. Thomas Hooker"},{"type":"civic_peer","related_id":"X00090","display_label":"Both in the Adventurers Party 1635; both Ha